           | Paragraphs have a readable line-height and clear margins. In the first paragraph of the example you can see the &lt;strong&gt; and &lt;em&gt; tags at work. The &lt;b&gt; and &lt;i&gt; are also supported, though they have been redefined in HTML5 and are in most cases not what you want. Find out more in the section title <q>What they're for</q> <cite>W3C,2010</cite> from <a href="http://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-b-and-i-tags" target="_blank">Using &lt;b&gt; and &lt;i&gt; elements</a> for more.
         P    
           | In the last sentence of the previous paragraph was an example of an inline quote with the &lt;q&gt; tag with actual &ldquo;quotes&rdquo; as well as an inline citation with the &lt;cite&gt; tag.
